<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n36213c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36213c">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36213c"> 213(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> kill all 6 footers</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">In consequence of which enormities they <font color="green">[the wicked giants]</font> fell under the high displeasure of chivalry, and all true, loyal and gallant knights were instructed to attack and <mark>slay outright any miscreant they might happen to find above six feet high</mark>, which is doubtless one reason why the race of large men is nearly extinct, and the generations of later ages are so exceedingly small. <small> Washington Irving, <a name="WINY" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#WINY"><cite title="source">A History of New York, by Diedrich Knickerbocker</cite></a> (ed. unknown) 267</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
